"{\"uid\": \"article18\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"to Europe's single market - would only lead to the continued unraveling of the EU.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 79, \"end\": 81, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7939625878147057e-14, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So what should be done?\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would suggest several measures, both to reduce the risks of catastrophic feedback loops in the short term and to maximize the benefits of reform in the long term.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First, stop the refugee surge by ending the Syrian war immediately.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This can be accomplished by ending the CIA-Saudi alliance to overthrow Bashar al-Assad, thereby enabling Assad (with Russian and Iranian backing) to defeat the Islamic State and stabilize Syria (with a similar approach in neighboring Iraq).\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"America's addiction to regime change (in Afghanistan, Iraq, Libya, and Syria) is the deep cause of Europe's refugee crisis.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"End the addiction, and the recent refugees could return home.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, stop NATO's expansion to Ukraine and Georgia.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new Cold War with Russia is another US-contrived blunder with plenty of European naivet\\\\\\\\u00e9 attached.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Closing the door on NATO expansion would make it possible to ease tensions and normalize relations with Russia, stabilize Ukraine, and restore focus on the European economy and the European project.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Third, do not punish Britain.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, police national and EU borders to stop illegal migrants.\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not xenophobia, racism, or fanaticism.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is common sense that countries with the world's most generous social-welfare provisions (Western Europe) must say no to millions (indeed hundreds of millions) of would-be migrants.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same is true for the US.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fourth, restore a sense of fairness and opportunity for the disaffected working class and those whose livelihoods have been undermined by financial crises and the outsourcing of jobs.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This means following the social-democratic ethos of pursuing ample social spending for health, education, training, apprenticeships, and family support, financed by taxing the rich and closing tax havens, which are gutting public revenues and exacerbating economic injustice.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also means finally giving Greece debt relief, thereby ending the long-running eurozone crisis.\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fifth, focus resources, including additional aid, on economic development, rather than war, in low-income countries.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Uncontrolled migration from today's poor and conflict-ridden regions will become overwhelming, regardless of migration policies, if climate change, extreme poverty, and lack of skills and education undermine the development potential of Africa, Central America and the Caribbean, the Middle East, and Central Asia.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All of this underscores the need to shift from a strategy of war to one of sustainable development, especially by the US and Europe.\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walls and fences will not stop millions of migrants fleeing violence, extreme poverty, hunger, disease, droughts, floods, and other ills.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2752, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only global cooperation can do that.\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2789, \"entities\": []}]}"